name: Study CDISC01_1, Data Definitions V-1
description: Data Definitions for CDISC01-01 SDTM datasets. This metadata version contains only a subset of datasets compared to the prior version. The metadata provided is only intended to illustrate most Define-XML 2.1 new features and not meant to serve as a comprehensive example of all metadata expected to be defined to fully describe an SDTM dataset package.   Notes:   1) Supplemental documents released in prior Define-XML versions were not updated to reflect changes to the metadata.    2) This example is prepared for a context other than submission; however, still using the approach of non-standard variables prepared as supplemental qualifiers datasets.
studyDescription: CDISC Test Study Modified to illustrate Define-XML 2.1 features

methods.name: Algorithm to derive CLSIG
methods.description: Only created if value qualifies as potentially clinically significant high or low based on the high and low ranges specified in the Statistical Analysis Plan.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive ECENDY
methods.description:
ECENDY = ECENDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if ECENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. 
ECENDTC - RFSTDTC if ECENDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive EXDOSE
methods.description:
If ARMCD=WONDER10 then EXDOSE = Number of Tablets per Day (QVAL where QNAM=SMNO) * 10.
If ARMCD=WONDER20 then EXDOSE = Number of Tablets per Day (QVAL where QNAM=SMNO) * 20.
If ARMCD=PLACEBO then EXDOSE = 0.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive EXDOSU
methods.description: Derived from ARM, ARMCD - equal to mg

methods.name: Algorithm to derive EXENDY
methods.description:
EXENDY = EXENDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if EXENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC.
EXENDTC - RFSTDTC if EXENDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive EXSTDY
methods.description:
EXSTDY = EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if EXSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC.
EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC if EXSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive EXTRT
methods.description: Derived from ARM, ARMCD

methods.name: Algorithm to derive LBBLFL
methods.description:
Safety subjects only: LBBLFL = "Y" for last record with non Null LBORRES on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).
Null otherwise.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive LBDY
methods.description: LBDY = LBDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if LBDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. LBDTC - RFSTDTC if LBDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive LBNRIND
methods.description: Reference Range Indicator based upon standard results and ranges.

methods.name: Algorithm to assign RACE
methods.description: Selected value converted to upper case to match CT.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive RDOMAIN
methods.description: Domain abbreviation from where data originated.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive RFENDTC
methods.description:
RFENDTC = termination date, for safety subjects.
Null for screen failures.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive RFSTDTC
methods.description:
RFSTDTC = first date/time of study drug, for safety subject.
Null for screen failures.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive the SAFETY population flag
methods.description: SAFETY = "Y" for randomized subjects who took at least one dose study medication. Null otherwise.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive SEQ
methods.description: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID in the domain.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive TSSEQ
methods.description: Sequential number identifying records within each TSPARM in the domain.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive USUBJID
methods.description: Concatenation of STUDYID and SUBJID

methods.name: Algorithm to derive VSBLFL
methods.description:
Safety subjects only: VSBLFL = "Y" for last record with non Null VSORRES on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).
Null otherwise.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive VSDY
methods.description: VSDY = VSDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if VSDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. VSDTC - RFSTDTC if VSDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive VSSTRESC
methods.description: Data collected in non-standard units (i.e. lbs, inches) is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units (kg, cm).

methods.name: Algorithm to derive VSSTRESN
methods.description: VSSTRESN = numeric value of VSSTRESC, when VSSTRESC contains numeric data.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XSBLFL
methods.description:
Safety subjects only: XSBLFL = "Y" for last record with non Null XSORRES on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).
Null otherwise.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XSDY
methods.description: XSDY = XSDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if XSDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. XSDTC - RFSTDTC if XSDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XSSTRESC
methods.description:
Data collected in non-standard units (i.e. lbs, inches) is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units (kg, cm).

BMI is calculated by the EDC system (operationally derived) as follows:
 round((XSSTRESN for weight/ (XSSTRESN for height / 100)^2), .01).

 Note: If height is not collected at a visit, use the height collected at screening.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XSSTRESN
methods.description: XSSTRESN = numeric value of XSSTRESC, when XSSTRESC contains numeric data.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XXBLFL
methods.description:
Safety subjects only: XXBLFL = "Y" for last record with non Null XXORRES on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).
Null otherwise.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XXDY
methods.description: XXDY = XXDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if XXDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. XXDTC - RFSTDTC if XXDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XXSTRESC
methods.description:
Data collected in non-standard units (i.e. lbs, inches) is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units (kg, cm).

BMI is calculated by the EDC system (operationally derived) as follows:

methods.name: Algorithm to derive XXSTRESN
methods.description: XXSTRESN = numeric value of XXSTRESC, when XXSTRESC contains numeric data.

_odmMetadata.Name: Study CDISC01_1, Data Definitions V-1
_odmMetadata.StudyDescription: CDISC Test Study Modified to illustrate Define-XML 2.1 features

COM.ARM.text: Assigned from TA.ARM based on ARMCD.

COM.ARMCD.text: Assigned based on Randomization Number. See Note 2.1

COM.COUNTRY.text: This is a subset of the ISO-3166_Country_Codes codelist

COM.CT1.text: Assuming the CT was not upversioned for this study

COM.CT2.text: The CT version applicable for the new Domain is the 2015-12-18 version

COM.CT2-EC.text: The Domain codelist was updated when SDTMIG 3.2 became production. Referencing a newer CT version that includes the revised codelist

COM.CT2-SEX.text: The term "UN" was changed to "UNDIFERENTIATED" for codelist "SEX" on the 2014-03-28 CT release. Referencing the codelist from a newer release since the new release includes other codelists used in the study.

COM.DOMAIN.DI.text: The DI domain is included to illustrate the use of a separate complementary SDTMIG. In this example, the device ID is referenced from a Findings Domain (XS).

COM.IDVAR.text: Name of the variables for the related records.

COM.IDVARVAL.text: Value of identifying variable described in IDVAR.

COM.ISO3166.text: The code values used are the Alpha-3 codes

COM.LBNRIND.text: Assuming the LBNRIND is derived by the vendor

COM.LBORRES.text: Origin specified at Value Level Metadata

COM.LBORRESU(Repeated).text: Note this example does not include VLM for this variable since it is just an example and the way to specify VLM is illustrated for LBORRESU.

COM.RACE.text: Note that the study protocol has been amended to not allow the specification of other race per current regulatory requirements. Refer to FDA Guidance XYZ and PMDA Guidance P-XYZ.

COM.RESU.text: Planned Numeric tests were not performed.

COM.STD1.text: The CDISC01 study was modeled on a very old SDTMIG and no attempt was done yet to upversion it to a newer SDTMIG

COM.STD2.text: As an example, the CDISC01 study was adjusted to include a new Domain available in SDTM IG 3.2

COM.STD3.text: As an example, the CDISC01 study was adjusted to include a new Domain available in SDTMIG-MD 1.0. The XS Domain is expected to reference the device used with variable SPDEVID.

COM.STD5.text: This is the CDISC CT Package 59 (2025-03-28) associated to the CDISC Define-XML Specification Version 2.1.9.

COM.STUDY.DATA.text: The data submitted only includes subjects in the USA since other sites did not enroll any subjects.

COM.SUBJECTDATA-JOIN-DM.text: Join any Subject Level dataset with the Demographics dataset based on [IG.datasetname]IT.USUBJID = [IG.DM]IT.USUBJID, assuming 'IG.datasetname' is the OID of the ItemGroupDef that defines the subject-level dataset to be joined with the Demographics dataset.

COM.VS.VISITNUM.text: Assigned from the TV domain based on the VISIT

COM.VSSTRESC.text: Testing a comment in addition to a method: BMI is derived and the specific method is provided at VLM

COM.VSSTRESN.text: Testing a comment in addition to a method: BMI is operationally derived and the specific method is provided at VLM

COM.VSSTRESU.text: Standard units consistent with CDISC controlled terminology

COM.XX.text: Special domain contingent on rare conditions observed.

IT.LB.LBORRES.HCT.LBSPEC.BLOOD.CRF.originDescription: From Local lab (LB.LBNAM="LOCAL LAB"). Note that the CRF page reference is given only for illustration purposes. The sample acrf.pdf does not include the local lab CRF page.
